article.description:
Justyna Podziemska scored 20 points to lead 
Wyoming to a 73-35 victory over Westminster College on
Wednesday night.
article.headline: Podziemska notches 20 as No. 25 Wyoming rolls
article.linkText: Podziemska notches 20 as No. 25 Wyoming rolls
article.story:
LARAMIE, Wyo. -- Justyna Podziemska scored 20 points to lead
Wyoming (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) to a 73-35 victory over Westminster College on
Wednesday night.

      Jodi Bolerjack added 13 points, while Hillary Carlson had 12 for
the Cowgirls (11-1).

      The Griffins (12-2) held the game close early in the first half,
but a 3-pointer by Podziemska sparked a 28-12 run that gave the
Cowgirls a 39-24 halftime lead.

      The Cowgirls opened the second half with a 24-3 run and took a
61-27 lead before head coach Joe Legerski sat his starters for the
final 10 minutes of the game.

      Shannon Evans led Westminster College with 18 points.
